---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'July 20, 2026';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy - Savelle Design"
  description="How savelledesign.com collects, uses, and protects your information."
>
  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-zinc-900 mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-zinc-500 mb-12">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <div class="prose prose-lg prose-zinc max-w-none
        prose-headings:font-bold prose-headings:text-zinc-900
        prose-h2:text-2xl prose-h2:mt-10 prose-h2:mb-4
        prose-p:text-zinc-600 prose-p:leading-relaxed
        prose-strong:text-zinc-900 prose-strong:font-semibold
        prose-ul:text-zinc-600
        prose-a:text-zinc-900 prose-a:no-underline hover:prose-a:text-zinc-600">
        <p>
          This Privacy Policy explains how Savelle McThias (&ldquo;I,&rdquo; &ldquo;me,&rdquo; or
          &ldquo;Savelle Design&rdquo;) collects, uses, and protects information when you visit
          savelledesign.com or contact me about design and development services.
        </p>

        <h2>Information I collect</h2>
        <p><strong>Information you provide.</strong> When you submit the contact form, take the
          UX Health Check, email me, or discuss a project, you may share your name, email address,
          project details, and any other information you choose to include.</p>
        <p><strong>Information collected automatically.</strong> Like most websites, this site may
          use analytics to understand how visitors use it. This can include your approximate
          location, device and browser type, pages viewed, and referring links. This data is
          aggregated and is not used to personally identify you.</p>

        <h2>How I use information</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>To respond to your inquiries and provide design and development services</li>
          <li>To understand and improve how the site performs</li>
          <li>To send information you have requested or that relates to work in progress</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Third-party services</h2>
        <p>This site relies on a few trusted third parties, each governed by its own privacy policy:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Google Apps Script</strong> — processes and stores submissions from the contact
            form and UX Health Check
            (<a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">privacy policy</a>)</li>
          <li><strong>Google Analytics</strong> — website usage measurement, where enabled
            (<a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">privacy policy</a>)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>I do not sell your personal information.</p>

        <h2>Cookies</h2>
        <p>The site and any analytics provider may use cookies or similar technologies. You can
          control cookies through your browser settings; disabling them may affect some features
          of the site.</p>

        <h2>Data retention</h2>
        <p>I keep the information you provide only as long as needed to respond to you, deliver
          services, meet legal and accounting obligations, and resolve disputes.</p>

        <h2>Your choices</h2>
        <p>You may request access to, correction of, or deletion of the personal information you
          have shared with me by emailing the address below. You can also opt out of analytics
          tracking using browser tools or extensions.</p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>Questions about this policy? Email
          <a href="mailto:savellem@gmail.com">savellem@gmail.com</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
